   Species richness in each plant group was modelled separately by generalised linear models (GLM), using the recorded explanatory variables as predictors. Pond area, water depth and water chemical variables were the most important predictors of hydrophyte and helophyte species richness, followed by fluctuation and human impact variables such as liming and presence of ducks and fish. Pond margin area and geographical variables were significant predictors of richness of terrestrial species of pond margins.
